Show HN: CodeLink: create links to blocks of code in your IDE
text: Small team down here in South New Zealand just launched CodeLink. In short its an IDE (VSCode/JetBrains) plugin that lets you share blocks of code that link directly to the code inside your IDE or repo. We use it all the time and think its pretty nifty tech that lets you understand someone’s code in context very quickly.  we’re hoping to keep refining it to make it better and more useful.

Ask HN: Best mental health resources for founders?
text:
Founders have 2-10x more “mental health issues” than civilians and a large number of failures are do to arguably preventable founder conflicts / mental health.

I currently support some of the biggest names in tech (successful unicorn’s) in 1:1 coaching, but I’m curious about what resources other founders are using?

We’ve launched a scalable private group for founders that is much more accessible than the $50k-$100k my 1:1 work is, and I’d like to know what other options folks consider.

Can be founder specific or just things cobbled together.

Thanks!
